# Golden Reference — UC-Pipeline Wiki Output Shape (8 sections)

> **Read this file ONCE before Phase 5 generates documentation.** It defines the shape,
> structure, and quality bar. Your output must match this skeleton. If it doesn't, fix it
> before writing to disk.

**Why 8 sections (was 6)**: The earlier 6-section skeleton produced mechanical SQL re-emissions
without business meaning. The DWH framework (`dwh-semantic-doc/GOLDEN-REFERENCE.mdc`) produces
rich wikis precisely because it splits §1 Business Meaning from §2 Business Logic (per-concept)
and §3 Query Advisory. The UC pipeline now follows the same 8-section split, with prose
synthesized under the **Grounded Synthesis Contract** (§6 in `05-generate-doc.mdc`).

## A. The Skeleton

```markdown
---
object: main.{schema}.{name}                       ← FQN
schema: {schema}
framework: uc-pipeline-doc
table_type: VIEW | MANAGED | EXTERNAL | MATERIALIZED_VIEW
format: DELTA | null
column_count: N
row_count: N | null
generated_at: <ISO8601>
upstreams:
  - main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction
  - main.dwh.dim_position
writer:
  kind: view_definition | NOTEBOOK | JOB | PIPELINE | UC_FUNCTION
  path: "/Workspace/Repos/.../foo.py"
  source_code_snapshot: "_discovery/source_code/v_fact_customeraction_enriched.sql"
concept_count: N                                   ← from concepts.json (Phase 4.5)
formula_count: N                                   ← from formulas.json (Phase 4.6)
tier_breakdown:
  tier1_columns: N
  tier2_columns: N
  tier3_columns: N
  tier4_columns: N
  tier5_columns: N
  unverified_columns: N
---

# {bare object name}

> {1-2 sentence summary: row count, what this object adds vs upstream, primary upstream, writer pattern}.

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **UC Object** | `main.{schema}.{name}` |
| **Type** | VIEW | MANAGED | … |
| **Format** | DELTA | n/a |
| **Owner** | (from UC DESCRIBE EXTENDED) |
| **Row count** | N rows | n/a |
