## B. Quality Assertions — Machine-Checkable

After writing, verify EVERY assertion before saving:

| # | Assertion | How to Check | Hard/Soft |
|---|-----------|-------------|-----------|
| 1 | All 8 `## N.` sections present (1 through 8) | Count `## 1.` through `## 8.` headers | HARD |
| 2 | Every Element description ends with `(Tier N — source)` | Grep for `\(Tier [1-5U] —` in Section 4 | HARD |
| 3 | Element table has 5 columns: `# \| Element \| Type \| Nullable \| Description` | Check header row | HARD |
| 4 | Element count matches `column_count` in frontmatter | Compare table-row count vs frontmatter | HARD |
| 5 | Section 5.2 has pipeline ASCII diagram | Check for code block with `→` or `▼` | HARD |
| 6 | Footer has Concepts + Formulas + tier breakdown counts matching frontmatter | Compare `*Generated:` line vs frontmatter | HARD |
| 7 | §1 Business Meaning has at least 3 paragraphs (blank-line-separated text blocks) | Count paragraphs in §1 | HARD |
| 8 | §2 Business Logic has one `### 2.N` subsection per concept in `concepts.json` | Compare subsection count vs `concept_count` frontmatter | HARD |
| 9 | Property table has at least UC Object, Type, Writer, Primary upstream, Concepts | Check for these rows | HARD |
| 10 | `.review-needed.md` does NOT contain `## 4. Elements` | If it does, content is in the WRONG file | HARD |
| 11 | `.lineage.md`, `concepts.json`, `formulas.json` all exist and were written BEFORE `.md` | Check file existence + mtime | HARD |
| 12 | For passthrough columns, the description text MATCHES the upstream wiki's Element description byte-for-byte | Grep upstream wiki and diff | HARD |
| 13 | For Tier-2 columns, the description contains the formula from `formulas.json` (substring match on `formula` field) | Grep description against formula text | HARD |
| 14 | For pure-passthrough VIEWs (all transforms in `{passthrough,rename,cast}`), §2 collapses to "Pure passthrough of {upstream} — no transformation logic." | Check transform classifications in `.lineage.md` | SOFT |

**If ANY HARD assertion fails: delete the file and regenerate. Do not patch.**

## C. Dictionary Inline Values Rule

Same as `dwh-semantic-doc/GOLDEN-REFERENCE.mdc` §C:

| Dictionary Size | Rule | Example |
|----------------|------|---------|
| **<=15 distinct values** | Inline key=value pairs in the description | `1=Regular, 2=CopyMe, 3=Social Index, 4=Fund (Dictionary.MirrorType)` |
| **>15 distinct values** | Name the join target only, describe what it represents | `FK to dim_country. Resolves to country name.` |

## D. Tier Suffix Convention — UC Pipeline Specifics

The tier suffix `(Tier N — origin)` lives at the END of every Element description. Use these origin patterns:

| Column situation | RIGHT | WRONG |
|---|---|---|
| Passthrough of a DWH gold-mirror column whose origin is `Trade.PositionTbl` | `(Tier 1 — Trade.PositionTbl)` | `(Tier 1 — main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction)` |
| Passthrough of a column with no upstream wiki (genuinely new column added in this UC object) | `(Tier 2 — main.{schema}.{this_object})` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| CASE/CAST/arithmetic over an upstream column | `(Tier 2 — from main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction)` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| Multi-source UNION ALL | `(Tier 2 — from main.dwh...fact_customeraction, main.etoro_kpi_prep.passive_actions_enriched)` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| Pure literal (`current_date`, `1`, `'PROD'`) | `(Tier 2 — literal)` | `(Tier 2 — view DDL)` |
| join_enriched column from a join source with a wiki | inherit join source's origin tier tag | `(Tier 1 — JOIN)` |

The origin **always** names a data-producing entity (a table, or for the literal/synthesized case, the keyword `literal` or `computed in source`). It never names "view DDL" or "notebook" as such — those are evidence types cited inside the description; the tier suffix names the data origin.

## E. Anti-Patterns — What Drift Looks Like

### E1. Missing Tier Suffix

```
WRONG: | 3 | enrichment_flag | STRING | YES | Flag for copy vs manual actions |
RIGHT: | 3 | enrichment_flag | STRING | YES | Copy-vs-manual classifier on ActionTypeID. `CASE WHEN ActionTypeID IN (2,5) THEN 'copy' ELSE 'manual' END`. (Tier 2 — from `main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction`) |
```

### E2. Synapse-mirror as origin

```
WRONG: | 1 | HistoryID | BIGINT | NO | Source-system history id. (Tier 1 — main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction) |
RIGHT: | 1 | HistoryID | BIGINT | NO | Source-system history id from `History.Credit` (non-unique — never use as PK). (Tier 1 — History.Credit) |
```

Tier transitivity: the Synapse mirror is a RELAY, not the origin. Always inherit through.

### E3. Wiki content in sidecar

```
WRONG: Writing the Elements table into {Object}.review-needed.md
RIGHT: The .md file gets the full 8-section wiki. The .review-needed.md gets ONLY
       UNVERIFIED items, Tier 4 candidates needing review, parser warnings, and
       reviewer correction notes. It is a lightweight checklist, NOT a duplicate wiki.
```

### E4. Bloated Section 2 for passthrough views

```
WRONG: Filling Section 2 with subsections that just re-describe the upstream's logic.
RIGHT: For pure-passthrough VIEWs: "Pure passthrough of `main.dwh.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_dwh_dbo_fact_customeraction` — no transformation logic. See upstream wiki for source-system rules: knowledge/synapse/Wiki/DWH_dbo/Tables/Fact_CustomerAction.md." Section 2 = 1 sentence.
```

### E5. §2 subsection without a concept anchor

```
WRONG: ### 2.1 Some pattern I noticed in the SQL
RIGHT: Every ### 2.N subsection corresponds to exactly one concept in concepts.json.
       If you have a §2 subsection without a matching concept, EITHER add the concept
       to concepts.json (re-run Phase 4.5) OR remove the subsection.
```

### E6. Missing concepts.json / formulas.json

```
WRONG: Generating §1/§2/§3 without consulting concepts.json or formulas.json.
RIGHT: Phase 5 reads `_discovery/concepts/{obj}.json` and `_discovery/formulas/{obj}.json`
       AS HARD INPUTS. Missing either = STOP and run Phase 4.5 / 4.6.
```
